N2  - Organizational contingency theory has developed from two separate bodies of research. This article examines the possible benefits of combining one approach emphasizing individual differences (the ?complex man? perspective), and a second approach emphasizing organizational and/or environmental differences (the ?complex organization? perspective). Research indicates that the complex organization approach deserves to be more fully developed. Future directions for contingency research are discussed.
AB  - Organizational contingency theory has developed from two separate bodies of research. This article examines the possible benefits of combining one approach emphasizing individual differences (the ?complex man? perspective), and a second approach emphasizing organizational and/or environmental differences (the ?complex organization? perspective). Research indicates that the complex organization approach deserves to be more fully developed. Future directions for contingency research are discussed.
