N2  - Forces in the industrial relations setting and within organizations which influence the form and content of worker participation are examined. Values, socio-political climate, economic conditions, and bargaining structures are identified as especially salient contextual forces, in addition to organizational dimensions of size, centralization, and technology. Drawing upon a comparative analysis of Western Nations, testable propositions are presented concerning factors which encourage or inhibit participation.
